description: Chhattisgarh high court granted a 29-year-old man, born to an unmarried woman, his legitimate status and rights. Overturning a family court's decision, the high court declared him entitled to legal benefits from his biological father. The man had sought maintenance and property share, which the family court initially denied, prompting his appeal.
title: HC gives man born out of wedlock all legal benefits from biological dad

description: BJP announced candidates for nine out of 12 Rajya Sabha seats in upcoming bypolls, including former Congress members Ravneet Singh Bittu from Rajasthan and Kiran Choudhary from Haryana. Other candidates include George Kurian for MP, Mamata Mohanta for Odisha, and Manan Kumar Mishra for Bihar. The seats became vacant due to recent Lok Sabha elections.
title: Bittu & Kiran Choudhary among BJP's Rajya Sabha poll picks

description: Former Jharkhand CM Champai Soren, after posting cryptic social media messages, expressed disappointment with JMM leadership for his removal as CM. On Tuesday, four JMM MLAs close to Champai pledged their allegiance to current CM Hemant Soren, quashing rumors of a rift and potential BJP crossover. Champai denied contacting BJP leaders during his Delhi visit.
title: Champai finds himself alone as 4 ‘loyalists’ swear allegiance to Hemant
Withdrawal of lateral entry ad a win for social justice: Stalin
Chirag Paswan: Govt has reaffirmed commitment to SCs, STs, OBCs

description: Congress president Mallikarjun Kharge hailed the withdrawal of the lateral entry scheme as a significant victory for social justice, crediting opposition protests for this and other recent rollbacks. He emphasised the importance of remaining vigilant against BJP-RSS efforts to undermine reservations. Rahul Gandhi reiterated the party's commitment to breaking the 50% reservation ceiling based on a caste census.
title: Pushed back govt, but must stay alert on RSS-BJP: Cong on lateral entry

description: The Modi government swiftly cancelled its lateral recruitment ad following opposition allegations it would undermine caste quotas. The BJP initially defended the policy but reconsidered, especially with state elections looming. The move appears to address concerns raised by opposition campaigns and recent Supreme Court discussions on caste and quotas.
title: Opposition trumps government's lateral entry plan with quota card

description: India and Malaysia elevated their ties to a comprehensive strategic partnership during talks between PM Narendra Modi and Anwar Ibrahim. The nations signed nine MoUs focusing on various issues including worker welfare, defense cooperation, and counter-terrorism. Modi emphasized mutual defense interests and a commitment to Asean centrality. India also announced a rice allocation for Malaysia.
title: India, Malaysia elevate ties to 'strategic partnership'
Engineering aspirant found dead in Kota hostel

description: The government had mandated that Centre-run hospitals limit patient attendants to one or two and suggested a pass system to control overcrowding. The directive was prompted by security concerns, emphasising restricted access, secured premises for female staff, and increased security personnel. An official also noted hospitals' vulnerability to security risks despite their accessibility.
title: Central-govt-run hosps will now allow only up to 2 attendants with patient

description: Trinamool Congress welcomed the Supreme Court's order regarding the rape-murder case at RG Kar Medical College, calling it a timely intervention needed across India. TMC urged protesting doctors to resume work for patients' sake, and expressed no objection to the deployment of central forces. TMC also urged the CBI to expedite its chargesheet against the main accused, Sanjay Roy.
title: TMC hails SC order, says it’s meant for entire country, not just Bengal

description: The Supreme Court ordered immediate deletion of posts revealing the identity of a doctor sexually assaulted and murdered in Kolkata. The decision followed a PIL, citing violations of SC's 2018 ruling and Section 72 of Bhartiya Nyaya Sanhita. The court emphasised privacy and dignity, directing social and electronic media compliance.
title: Remove victim’s name, videos from electronic, social media: SC
Whistleblower called to Kolkata as SIT starts graft probe against Ghosh

description: Trinamool Congress's MP Sukhendu Sekhar Roy deleted contentious posts on X following Kolkata Police's summons over misinformation allegations. He spoke with the police and agreed to remove three posts related to the RG Kar incident. The state assured no coercive action against him. The court recorded this mutual agreement, resulting in no further judicial intervention.
title: TMC MP deletes posts; won't act against him, state tells Calcutta HC

description: An umbrella body of Durga Puja organisers in West Bengal has urged for the harshest punishment for those guilty in the rape and murder of a junior doctor at RG Kar Medical College. They pleaded not to link Durga Puja with the incident, emphasising the festival's significant economic impact and the livelihoods it supports.
title: 'Livelihood of millions depend on Durga Puja': Organisers amid boycott calls

description: An FIR for criminal conspiracy and cheating was lodged against former RG Kar Medical College principal Sandip Ghosh. Alleged to have colluded with contractors for projects, Ghosh's dealings came under scrutiny following a junior doctor's rape-murder. A Special Investigation Team will investigate financial irregularities during his tenure from 2021 onwards.
title: Criminal conspiracy, cheating & DA case slapped on ex-principal Ghosh

description: The body of a PGT doctor was discovered at RG Kar Medical College, initially reported as a suicide by the hospital before being identified as a case of rape and murder. Questions arose about why former principal Sandip Ghosh's office misled the parents. The incident is under scrutiny for the delayed and misleading communication.
title: Who spread suicide claim? Many say story originated in ex-principal’s office

description: The body of a postgraduate resident doctor was found at RG Kar Medical College, leading to a murder alarm by her parents. Despite being notified early, an FIR was lodged only late at night. Procedural delays by Kolkata police in filing the formal complaint have sparked scrutiny. Authorities are now being pressurised to clarify the reason behind the delay.
title: Parents cried murder at 3pm but FIR was lodged much later. Why the delay?

description: Security forces in Rajouri, J&K, discovered an underground terrorist hideout in Sagrawat forest, seizing ammunition and items including magazines, bullets, a communication set, and essential supplies. The operation, based on intelligence inputs, was conducted by a joint team comprising police, SoG, CRPF, and the Army’s Rashtriya Rifles.
title: Underground terrorist hideout busted in J&K’s Rajouri, ammo seized

description: Political activities in J&K ramped up after the EC announced the first phase of assembly elections on September 18, ending a decade-long gap. Major parties like NC, PDP, Congress, and BJP are in the fray, while Engineer Rashid's AIP gains momentum. Key resignations and shifting allegiances could influence the results significantly.
title: Political activities surge as EC issues J&K poll notification

description: CRPF inspector Kuldeep Kumar, aged 54, was killed in a terrorist attack in Udhampur, J&K. A wreath-laying ceremony honored him, attended by senior officials and his community. Kumar served 34 years and was a wrestler. He is survived by his family. Officials continue searching for the terrorists who escaped.
title: Udhampur attack: Tributes to slain CRPF officer, search ops continue

description: India and Japan have agreed to enhance their defence-industrial collaboration, particularly focusing on the 'Unicorn' stealth antenna system for warships. They also aim to improve military interoperability through joint exercises and cooperation in space and cyber domains. The partnership is seen as crucial for maintaining peace and stability in the Indo-Pacific region.
title: India, Japan commit to boosting defence tech collaboration at ‘2+2’ dialogue

description: Telecom operators like Airtel, Reliance Jio, and Vodafone-Idea pushed to bring messaging and video call apps under telecom licenses, citing their significant contribution to data traffic. The Broadband India Forum countered, calling it discriminatory and unconstitutional.
title: 'Bringing OTT apps under telecom licence is violation of Constitution as ...'

description: The Reservation Bachao Sangharsh Samiti organized a Bharat Bandh on August 21, 2024, in response to a Supreme Court ruling allowing sub-categories within SC/ST reservations. Supported by various SC/ST groups, the bandh saw widespread participation. Authorities ramped up security to maintain order, although essential services like healthcare and public transport remained operational.
title: Schools closed tomorrow due to Bharat Bandh?
World’s oldest person Maria Branyas dies at 117

description: On August 21, 2024, a Bharat Bandh is being observed by the Reservation Bachao Sangharsh Samiti due to a Supreme Court decision on SC/ST reservations.
title: Bharat Bandh: Are banks & post offices open on August 21, 2024?
Training aircraft goes missing mid-air in Jharkhand's Saraikela; search operation launched

description: The UPSC withdrew advertisements for 45 lateral entry jobs due to opposition from JD(U) and LJP regarding caste reservations. This decision underscores the coalition's influence on Modi's governance in his third term, marking a shift from his earlier terms where BJP held the majority.
title: Govt's UPSC 'lateral entry' U-turn: Coalition compulsion or opposition pressure?

description: Donald Trump intensified his efforts to undermine Kamala Harris by questioning her background and eligibility. He criticized her father's Marxist ties and accused Harris of socialist ideologies. These actions echo his past tactics against minority politicians, causing a rift among moderate Republicans and leading some to endorse Harris.
title: Troll patrol: Trump and Harris taunt each other in toxic campaign
RBI chief Shaktikanta Das ranked top central banker globally
Underground terrorist hideout busted Rajouri; here's what forces found
'Trump will win if ... ': Why ex-Obama strategist said this about US prez polls
Court orders arrest of AAP MP Sanjay Singh, others for missing hearing

description: On August 18, 2024, the UPSC issued a recruitment advertisement for 45 lateral entry positions in various ministries, sparking debate and criticism from opposition leaders. The Central Government asked UPSC to cancel the recruitment, citing concerns over social justice and representation.
title: UPSC lateral entry explained: How it works, history and recent developments

description: The ICC Women's T20 World Cup is scheduled to take place from October 3 to 20. The Cricbuzz report said that the Bangladesh Cricket Board (BCB) has agreed to the shift but will continue to be the official host of the tournament.
title: ICC moves Women's T20 World from Bangladesh to UAE

description: Congress announced its openness to alliances with any party opposing BJP policies ahead of Jammu and Kashmir assembly elections. J&K Congress president Tariq Hameed Karra accused the BJP of damaging the union territory's communal fabric by inciting religious hatred. Karra also criticized the BJP for the recent rise in terror attacks in the region.
title: 'Ready to shake hands with anyone opposed to BJP': Congress on pre-poll alliance in J&K

description: Welcome to your daily dose of entertainment buzz! Grab your popcorn and dive into today’s top five highlights. From Jaya Bachchan’s emotional recollection of the Salim-Javed split, and Yuvraj Singh's inspiring biopic, to Aryan and AbRam Khan’s Rakhi celebration—here’s a look at the top news making waves in entertainment today!
title: Jaya Bachchan gets teary-eyed talking about Salim-Javed split: Top 5 entertainment news

description: Fresh off her double-medal win at the Paris Olympics, shooter Manu Bhaker has embarked on a nationwide tour to inspire young athletes. During her visit to Velammal Nexus School in Chennai, she shared her journey, emphasizing resilience after her Tokyo Olympics setback. Bhaker encouraged students to dream big, work hard, and consider sports as a viable career. She credited her mother as her biggest inspiration and highlighted the transformative power of sports in personal growth and confidence.
title: You don't have to become doctor or engineer: Manu Bhaker
Rajya Sabha bypolls: BJP fileds Ravneet Singh Bittu, George Kurian

description: With 15 wickets in the T20 World Cup, Jasprit Bumrah played a pivotal role in India's title triumph and Ricky Ponting heaped praise on the 30-year-old. Ponting said that there might have been a few concerns over Bumrah's longevity but he has only returned stronger from injuries.
title: Ponting's 'nightmare' praise for this India pacer

description: Reliance Jio introduced the JioTV+ app for smart TVs and launched a 2-in-1 offer, allowing users to connect two TVs with a single JioAirFiber connection. The app provides access to over 800 digital TV channels and 13 OTT apps with a single login. It is available for free download on leading Smart TV OS without additional charges.
title: Jio brings JioTV+ app on smartTVs, launches 2-in-1 offer
AIIMS Delhi issues SOP for handling patients with monkeypox symptoms

description: Mark Hamill assured fans that the Force was strong with Harris-Walz, while others who turned up included director Spike Lee, Amy Klobuchar, Golden State Warriors head coach Steve Kerr (referencing Steph Curry’s iconic “night night” line as a dig at Trump), and Sean Astin. Tony Goldwyn addressed the crowd, and James Taylor performed “You’ve Got a Friend.”
title: 'The Force is strong on Harris-Walz': Highlights of DNC Day 1
Mike Lynch was celebrating acquittal before violent storm hit
Modi 3.0: First meeting of council of ministers to be held on August 28

description: NASA astronauts Sunita Williams and Butch Wilmore were unexpectedly stranded on the ISS due to a malfunction in the Boeing Starliner's thrusters. Initially planned for an eight-day mission, concerns about their return have arisen with risks including failed reentry and potential vaporization if the capsule's angle is incorrect during descent.
title: Sunita Williams and Butch Wilmore may get vapourised says US
CCI warns Disney, Reliance merger will hurt rivals: Report

description: Fuentes, who had previously dined with former President Trump at Mar-a-Lago in 2022, directed his criticism at Vance and his family following Vance's decision to join Trump’s re-election campaign the previous month. Fuentes questioned Vance's commitment to white identity by pointing to his marriage to an Indian woman and their child’s name, Vivek.
title: White supremacist, who abused Usha Vance, praises Kamala Harris

description: Google announced the termination of its Play Security Reward Program from December 31. Established in 2017, the program incentivized security researchers to identify vulnerabilities in Android apps. Due to a decline in actionable reports, Google decided to wind it down. All reports submitted before August 31 will be reviewed and addressed before the program's official discontinuation on September 30.
title: Google is shutting this program 7 years after launch: Read email

description: Former Indian cricketer Robin Uthappa revealed his struggle with depression, describing it as more challenging than any on-field battle. In a social media post and YouTube video, Uthappa aimed to destigmatize mental health, urging others to seek help. His openness highlights the importance of addressing mental health in high-pressure environments.
title: 'Was ashamed of...': Uthappa's battle with depression

description: The Centre withdrew the UPSC lateral entry advertisement following criticisms from various political factions. BJP-NDA praised PM Modi for championing social justice, while the INDIA bloc hailed it as a victory for the Constitution. Concerns about reservations and favoritism influenced this decision.
title: UPSC lateral entry U-turn: NDA leaders thank PM Modi; oppn calls it victory of Constitution
J&K elections: PDP chief spokesperson Suhail Bukhari quits party

description: The Union Public Service Commission cancelled the advertisement for 45 lateral entry posts after a directive from the Centre. This affected positions of Joint Secretary, Director, and Deputy Director and was aimed at reassessing and aligning the lateral entry process with principles of equity and social justice.
title: UPSC withdraws lateral entry advertisement after Centre's directive
SC forms National Task Force to make blueprint for safety and facility for doctors

description: Ace Indian pistol shooter Manu Bhaker recently scripted history to become the first Indian athlete in post-independence era to win two Olympic medals in a single edition of the Olympic Games in Paris. Bhaker won bronze medals in 10m air pistol and mixed 10m air pistol events at Paris Olympics.
title: Watch: Manu Bhaker grooves to 'Kala Chashma'

description: The Supreme Court criticised the West Bengal government for delays in filing an FIR in the Kolkata rape-murder case. Governor CV Ananda Bose found relief in the court's remarks and prompted a jab at chief minister Mamata Banerjee. Bose also launched a mobile control room for the ongoing agitation regarding the incident, providing contact numbers for support.
title: 'Will Mamata ... ': Bengal guv after SC observations on rape-murder case

description: Former Pakistani pacer Wasim Akram and his wife Shaniera celebrated their 11th wedding anniversary with playful social media posts. Shaniera shared a humorous edited image of Wasim, blending teasing with affection. Wasim responded with a heartfelt tribute, expressing his love and gratitude for her. The couple’s lighthearted exchange charmed their followers.
title: Akram's wife teases Pak great with his bald picture

description: The BJP criticized Rahul Gandhi for not addressing the Kolkata rape-murder case during his visit to Rae Bareli. Gandhi chose to focus on the murder of a 22-year-old Dalit man in his constituency, stating he did not want to get distracted. BJP's Shehzad Poonawalla condemned Gandhi's response, highlighting the serious nature of the Kolkata case.
title: 'How dare he?' BJP attacks Rahul for 'distraction' remark on Kolkata rape-murder case

description: Mark Zuckerberg disclosed the email he used to create Facebook's first account, 'mzuckerb@fas.harvard.edu'. Initially meant for Harvard students, Facebook rapidly expanded beyond campus. Three accounts were tested before Zuckerberg's. Co-founders Chris Hughes and Dustin Moscovitz also had among the earliest accounts. The revelation sparked interest among users, reflecting on Facebook's remarkable journey.
title: Mark Zuckerberg shares email ID he used to create his first-ever account on FB

description: In 2007, fewer than 450 greater adjutant storks were left in Assam. Dr. Purnima Devi Barman led a conservation effort, enlisting 10,000 rural women in the 'Hargila Army' to protect the storks. By 2023, the population surged to over 1,800, earning Barman the 2024 Whitley Gold Award.
title: Dr Purnima Devi Barman’s conservation legacy and India’s rarest stork

description: The Union Public Service Commission (UPSC) is set to conduct the Combined Defence Services (CDS) 2 examination on September 1, 2024. The CDS 2 admit cards are expected to be available for download from the official UPSC website in late August. This exam aims to fill 459 vacancies across various defense academies, including the Indian Military Academy, Indian Naval Academy, Air Force Academy, and Officers’ Training Academy. The test will be held in three shifts, covering English, General Knowledge, and Mathematics. The selection process includes a written exam followed by a Service Selection Board (SSB) interview, which is conducted in two stages. Detailed preparation strategies, exam patterns, and guidelines are crucial for candidates to enhance their chances of success.
title: UPSC CDS 2 admit card soon: Check important details

description: A recent biography of Queen Elizabeth II by Craig Brown, unveiled the Queen's disapproval of former US President Donald Trump's behavior during his visits to the UK. She found him "very rude" and suggested he had an arrangement with his wife, Melania. The book also highlights the Queen's interactions with other controversial leaders.
title: Why did Queen Elizabeth II consider Trump ‘very rude’, reveals book

description: Rahul Gandhi voiced his protest against the killing of a 22-year-old Dalit man in Raebareli, criticizing the police for not taking action against the alleged mastermind. He met the victim's family and highlighted their grievances. So far, six arrests have been made in the case involving the death of Arjun Pasi on August 11.
title: 'Will not step back': Rahul meets family of murdered Dalit barber in UP

description: The Roxx is essentially the 5-door version of the standard Thar. It gets updated design, new features, bigger dimensions and more. In terms of design, it gets newly designed a double-stacked six-slot grille and the circular headlamps now feature LED projectors and C-shaped DRLs. While the fog lights and turn indicators retain their positions, they now have a sleeker appearance.
title: Mahindra Thar Roxx vs Thar three-door: Top five changes explained
SC agrees to hear West Bengal govt's plea against HC ruling quashing OBC status

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi held talks with Malaysian counterpart Anwar Ibrahim, leading to the elevation of India-Malaysia relations to a 'Comprehensive Strategic Partnership'. Modi highlighted the $5 billion Malaysian investment in India and emphasized the significant potential for economic cooperation, including bilateral trade in Rupee and Ringgit. This was Ibrahim's first visit to India as Prime Minister.
title: PM Modi holds bilateral talks with Malaysian counterpart Ibrahim

description: Numerous New Delhi shopping malls received bomb threat emails on Tuesday, prompting an immediate police investigation. Malls including Chanakya Mall, Select CityWalk, and others were targeted. Bomb Disposal Squads and fire tenders investigated but found no explosives. Initial findings suggest a pattern in the threats, similar to previous incidents. Authorities continue their inquiry into the source of the emails.
title: Several Delhi malls receive bomb threat mails

description: Ace wrestler Vinesh Phogat might contest in the upcoming Haryana Assembly elections, despite previously stating she wouldn't enter politics. Political parties are attempting to convince her. Her disqualification from the Paris Olympics due to being overweight prevented her from winning a gold medal.
title: Vinesh Phogat may contest polls against cousin Babita: Sources

description: The Supreme Court criticised the Mamata Banerjee-led West Bengal government and police for their handling of the rape and murder of a trainee doctor at Kolkata's RG Kar College. It questioned various aspects, including the FIR, actions against the college principal, vandalism near the crime scene, the initial suicide angle, and delays in allowing the parents to see the body.
title: 'We don't understand why ... ': 5 questions by SC in Kolkata doc rape-murder case

description: Ola Electric's stock has risen 107% from its IPO price, surpassing Tesla's valuation. Several long-term investors have pointed out that Ola, with a market capitalization of approximately Rs 66,000 crore as of this morning, is now more expensive than Tesla.
title: ‘Valuations more expensive than Tesla’: Ola Electric surges 107%

description: CM Punk and Drew McIntyre are set for a Strap Match at Bash in Berlin, as officially announced on Raw. CM Punk challenged McIntyre following a belt attack, and McIntyre accepted. This will be their second face-off after SummerSlam. The Strap Match has no disqualifications, and wrestlers must touch all four corners of the ring to win.
title: CM Punk vs Drew McIntyre Strap Match confirmed for Bash in Berlin 2024

description: Former Pakistan cricketer Basit Ali responded to Jasprit Bumrah's comments on fast bowlers in leadership roles. Ali highlighted that Kapil Dev and Imran Khan were all-rounders when they became captains. He cautioned Bumrah to focus on his bowling. He acknowledged Pat Cummins' success but noted the rarity of fast bowlers thriving as captains or coaches.
title: Jasprit Bumrah should not chase captaincy: Former Pakistan cricketer

description: Infosys has launched a 'power programme' in campus placements, offering packages up to Rs 9 lakh per annum. The initiative focuses on specialised skills like coding and AI, similar to TCS's 'Prime' programme.
title: Why Infosys is offering Rs 9 lakh salary to some freshers

description: Bollywood has significantly changed from its humble beginnings, spanning from the Golden Age, through the transformative 80s and 90s, into the new millennium with technological advances and globalization. Each era brought distinct themes and styles, impacting and reflecting societal changes. Nowadays, digital platforms enhance accessibility and drive content diversification, keeping Bollywood relevant. However, Bollywood has served as both a mirror and a mold, intertwining societal shifts with the magic of storytelling and entertainment.
title: Bollywood through the ages: How generations have shaped and been shaped by Indian cinema

description: Congress leader Rahul Gandhi paid tribute to his father, former Prime Minister Rajiv Gandhi, on his 80th birth anniversary. Rahul emphasized his admiration for his father's compassion and commitment to India's progress. Congress chief Mallikarjun Kharge also lauded Rajiv Gandhi's contributions, including the telecom revolution and the lowering of the voting age to 18 years.
title: 'Papa, will fulfil your dreams': Rahul's heartfelt tribute to father Rajiv Gandhi

description: Spinner R Sai Kishore, set to compete in the Duleep Trophy starting September 5, declared his readiness for Test cricket. Representing Team B, Kishore aims to secure a spot in the Indian Test squad for the Bangladesh series. He credited his rigorous pre-season training for boosting his confidence despite a brief IPL injury setback.
title: 'Put me in a Test match, I am ready': India spinner declares

description: Heavy rains on Tuesday morning caused widespread waterlogging in Delhi, leading to significant traffic snarls. Authorities advised using alternate routes due to disruptions at key locations like Minto Road, Nangloi, and Connaught Place. Areas such as ITO, Raisina, and Rajghat were also severely affected by the downpour, impacting commuters around the city.
title: 10 photos: Delhi submerged as rain triggers waterlogging, traffic snarls

description: The Supreme Court reprimanded the West Bengal government and Kolkata Police over their handling of the rape and murder case of a doctor at RG Kar Medical College. The court expressed concerns about the delay in filing an FIR and the incident's impact on women’s safety in workplaces. The case is now being investigated by the CBI. Court noted that the incident shocked the conscience of the nation.
title: 'Principal tried to pass it off as suicide': What SC said on Kolkata rape-murder case

description: Morne Morkel, at 39, took on the critical role of India's bowling coach. Facing the challenge of gaining the trust of seasoned players like Jasprit Bumrah, Morkel aims to leverage his experience from previous roles with Pakistan and New Zealand to bolster India's bowling unit and address both technical and mental aspects.
title: 'It's a matter of...': Albie on Morne's primary challenge as India coach

description: President Joe Biden made an emotional appearance at the DNC in Chicago, introduced by his daughter Ashley, who highlighted his commitment to women's rights. Ashley shared personal stories, emphasizing Biden's values of fairness and resilience. Biden, moved by her words, embraced her on stage, reflecting on family loss and his dedication to service.
title: 'OG girl dad': Biden brought to tears as daughter introduces him; watch video

description: The Democratic National Convention began with President Joe Biden endorsing Kamala Harris while addressing a variety of issues including Trump and the Gaza conflict. Biden, in his farewell speech, expressed support for Harris's campaign against Trump, emphasizing the need for preserving democracy. Key Democrats including Hillary Clinton and Nancy Pelosi were present, with Harris expressing gratitude and determination to win.
title: Joe Biden passes the baton to Kamala Harris: Takeaways from DNC's day 1

description: The upcoming biographical film will capture the life of former Indian cricketer Yuvraj Singh. Produced by Bhushan Kumar's T-Series and co-produced by Ravi Bhagchandka, the film will depict Yuvraj's cricketing milestones, including his six sixes in the 2007 T20 World Cup, his battle with cancer, and his return to the sport in 2012.
title: Yuvraj Singh's biographical movie set for celluloid release

description: Yuzvendra Chahal was recently seen enjoying a casual stroll with Ashish Nehra and Gaurav Kapur. They were captured singing the Bollywood song "Zindagi milke bitayenge". This viral video showcased their relaxed downtime away from the professional spotlight and delighted fans with their light-hearted interaction, reflecting camaraderie among sports and media personalities.
title: 'Zindagi milke bitayenge': Chahal, Nehra enjoy a stroll - Watch

description: Bootleggers exploited Maharashtra's dense forest terrain to smuggle illegal liquor into dry Gujarat. Covering a route from Daman to Nashik, the operations were meticulously planned, using multiple escort vehicles. Despite heavy seizures last year, the illicit trade persisted, causing fatalities among enforcement officials. The complex network and various routes pose significant challenges for law enforcement agencies.
title: Liquor flows into 'dry' Gujarat through Maharashtra's hilly terrain

description: Former US President Donald Trump announced on his Truth Social account that Vice President Kamala Harris will not participate in the Fox News debate on September 4. Trump criticized Harris for avoiding the debate and instead opted to participate in a Tele-Town Hall anchored by Sean Hannity in Pennsylvania. This follows President Biden's withdrawal from the Democratic nomination race.
title: Did Kamala Harris back out of September 4 debate? What Trump said

description: Pune Police apprehended two suspects for reportedly tampering with blood samples in the high-profile Porsche crash case. The crash, which took place on May 19, claimed the lives of two software engineers. The minor driver received bail from the Juvenile Justice Board, with conditions that emphasized road safety education and a training program.
title: Pune Porsche crash: 2 more arrested in connection with swapping of blood samples

description: India and Bangladesh's first Test in Chennai on September 19 recalls a historic event from November 2000. In their debut Test, Bangladesh faced India. Despite a strong first innings, Bangladesh fell short in the second, giving India an easy victory. The 1997 ICC Trophy win and infrastructure growth catapulted Bangladesh to Test status, eventually leading to this landmark match.
title: When 11 Bangladesh cricketers made their Test debuts against India

description: The batsman cemented his place in history as the first Samoan player to hit a century in international cricket. ​His game-changing knock of 132 runs from a mere 62 deliveries proved to be the catalyst for Samoa's second victory in the tournament. Visser's outstanding innings featured an impressive tally of 14 sixes.
title: Yuvraj’s record broken! Visser hits 39 runs in an over

description: Hillary Clinton criticised Donald Trump at the Democratic National Convention, highlighting his 34 felony convictions. She praised Vice President Kamala Harris for her prosecutorial work and drew a sharp contrast between Harris and Trump. Clinton called on Democrats to support Harris, emphasizing the historic opportunity for a woman to become president in 2024.
title: Watch: DNC crowd chants 'lock him up!' for Trump during Clinton’s speech

description: Amazon is considering launching a standalone app for Amazon Pay in India to enhance its usage and visibility. If implemented, the app would separate current payment features from Amazon's main e-commerce app. Plans are still under discussion with the NPCI.
title: Amazon may launch another app in India, here’s why

description: Former Indian cricket team captain Sourav Ganguly changed his social media profile pictures to black, showing solidarity with protests demanding justice for a trainee doctor raped and murdered at RG Kar Medical College. Ganguly clarified his earlier comments about Kolkata’s security, emphasizing it was a terrible incident and urged severe punishment for the culprits.

Rain soaks parts of Delhi-NCR; IMD predicts continued showers all week

description: US intelligence officials attributed the hacking of Donald Trump's presidential campaign to Iran, marking the first official accusation against Tehran for election hacking. The FBI and other federal agencies revealed that Iran also attempted to hack Kamala Harris's campaign. The hackers aimed to sow discord and influence the election outcome. Despite Iran's denial, allegations persist amid heightened US-Iran tensions. Confidential material from the Trump campaign was leaked to media outlets.
title: Iran behind Trump, Biden campaign hacks: US intel
Watch: Kamala Harris makes surprise appearance on day 1 of DNC

description: During a campaign stop, Donald Trump suggested Elon Musk for a key role in his potential future administration. He praised Musk's intelligence, describing him as a 'brilliant guy.' Earlier, the two discussed creating a government efficiency commission. However, Trump's plan to dismantle Biden's EV policies might pose challenges for Tesla, Musk's company.
title: 'If elected would offer Elon Musk Cabinet role or ... ': Trump

description: Rooted to his grounded nature, Dhoni has always made himself available to his close friends and even the fans whenever he is approached for a selfie or an autograph despite keeping largely quiet in his private life with family after retiring from international cricket in 2020. He continues to play the IPL, but the 43-year-old icon's availability for the next season is unsure.
title: MS Dhoni enjoys meal at a dhaba with close friends

description: Karun Nair turned back the clock in the most entertaining fashion for the Indian cricket fans on Monday with his unbeaten knock of 124 in just 48 balls for the Mysore Warriors against the Mangalore Dragons in the Maharaj Trophy T20 tournament at the M Chinnaswamy Stadium in Bengaluru. Warriors won the rain-shortened match by 27 runs (VJD method).
title: Karun Nair's blazing 124 off 48 balls deflates bowlers - Watch

description: The Centre increased security personnel by 25% in hospitals following the August 9 incident where a doctor was raped and murdered in Kolkata. A directive was issued to deploy marshals for security-related assistance. A committee will be set up to assess doctors' security, working hours, and facilities. Protesting doctors are urged to call off their strike as patient care suffers.
title: Security personnel at all central government hospitals to go up 25%
